  "observations": [
    "Three-pane shell: experiments tree (left sidebar) × runs table (center) × inspector/compare (right or modal)",
    "Run is the primary record — every artifact, metric and registered model traces back to a runId",
    "SQL-like filter bar (`metrics.x > 0.9 AND params.lr < 0.01`) is the canonical search surface, not a faceted filter panel",
    "Runs table has dynamic columns: user picks which params/metrics to materialize as columns, sortable on click",
    "Multi-select runs via checkbox → 'Compare' CTA opens a dedicated screen with parallel-coordinates, scatter, contour, and parallel-metrics plots",
    "Metrics are time-series (step × value) and rendered as line charts with overlay across selected runs — first-class temporal data, not scalar",
    "Run Detail uses tabbed layout (Overview / Parameters / Metrics / Artifacts / Tags / Source / Notes) — high-cardinality detail split by concern",
    "Artifacts viewer is a generic file tree with type-specific renderers (image preview, JSON viewer, prediction trace, eval table, dataset profile)",
    "'Register Model' is a CTA on Run Detail that lifts a run-output into the Model Registry — cross-domain promotion intent",
    "Model Registry has dual stage models: legacy stages (None/Staging/Production/Archived) and modern aliases (champion/challenger/latest, N-to-N)",
    "Stage transitions optionally gated by request-for-comment workflow (StageTransitionRequest with requester/approver/comment) when permissions enabled",
    "Model Version page exposes an inference snippet (Python + curl) with copy-to-clipboard — code is part of the UI surface",
    "Lineage is bidirectional and rendered as graph chips: Run ↔ ModelVersion ↔ Dataset",
    "Permissions are per-resource ACL (experiment, model) with three levels (CAN_READ/CAN_EDIT/CAN_MANAGE) — surface only in Databricks-managed variant",
    "Source code commit hash is shown as a hyperlink on every run — reproducibility witness",
    "Compare view does tabular diff (column per run) plus visual diff (parallel coordinates) — two materializations of the same comparison",
    "Top global search supports typed prefixes: `model:`, `tag:`, `metric:`, `version:>=N` — query language as primary navigation",
    "Charts on the experiment dashboard are user-configurable widgets (ChartPanel) — dashboard archetype with composable analytical slots",
    "Soft-delete pattern: experiments and runs have lifecycleStage (active/deleted) with restore intent rather than hard delete",
    "API-first model: `mlflow.start_run()` context manager creates runs from code, UI is a read-mostly observer with curation actions (rename, tag, register, archive)"
  ]
}